\par }\pard\plain \s16\qj\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \lang2057 {<#/>The Appellant, <name/>, was convicted after trial on two counts of robbery with violence contrary to section 296(2) of the Penal Cod
e by the Senior Resident Magistrate, Nairobi. <#/>He was sentenced to death. <#/>His co-Accused named in the charge was acquitted on both counts.
\par }\pard\plain \qj\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \lang2057 {<#/>Briefly, the prosecution case was that the 2}{\super nd}{ complainant, <name/> (P.W.1) who is a business lady, owned 
a butchery at Mlango Kubwa within Nairobi Area where she and her husband (P.W.3) had employed the 1}{\super st}{ complainant, <name/> (P.W.2).
\par <#/>On the night of 3}{\super rd}{ August, 1989 at about 10 p.m., while <name/> (P.W.2) was working in the said butchery, some four Afr
ican men entered the butchery and found him alone. <#/>One of the said men (not the Appellant) was armed with a pistol which he pointed at him as he ordered him to produce some money. <#/>When he replied that he did not  have any money, he was ordered to 
