e
 door using force. <#/>It does not occur to us that the learned trial magistrate had shifted the burden of proof to the Appellant. <#/>The case of <name/> -V-R (1965) EA 555 that was cited can therefore be easily distinguished. <#/>We uphold the convictio
n of the Appellant.
